theorem Topology.interiorClosure_inter_three_subset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B C : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∩ B ∩ C : Set X)) ⊆
      interior (closure A) ∩ interior (closure B) ∩ interior (closure C) := by
  intro x hx
  -- `x` lies in `interior (closure A)`
  have hxA : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure A) := by
    -- `A ∩ B ∩ C ⊆ A`
    have h_subset : (A ∩ B ∩ C : Set X) ⊆ A := by
      intro y hy; exact hy.1
    -- Monotonicity of `closure` and `interior`
    have h_int :
        interior (closure (A ∩ B ∩ C : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_mono (closure_mono h_subset)
    exact h_int hx
  -- `x` lies in `interior (closure B)`
  have hxB : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure B) := by
    -- `A ∩ B ∩ C ⊆ B`
    have h_subset : (A ∩ B ∩ C : Set X) ⊆ B := by
      intro y hy; exact hy.2.1
    have h_int :
        interior (closure (A ∩ B ∩ C : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure B) :=
      interior_mono (closure_mono h_subset)
    exact h_int hx
  -- `x` lies in `interior (closure C)`
  have hxC : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure C) := by
    -- `A ∩ B ∩ C ⊆ C`
    have h_subset : (A ∩ B ∩ C : Set X) ⊆ C := by
      intro y hy; exact hy.2.2
    have h_int :
        interior (closure (A ∩ B ∩ C : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure C) :=
      interior_mono (closure_mono h_subset)
    exact h_int hx
  exact And.intro hxA (And.intro hxB hxC)
